{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Late in January 1975,"},{"time":3400,"text":"a 17-year-old German girl\ncalled Vera Brandes"},{"time":7840,"text":"walked out onto the stage\nof the Cologne Opera House."},{"time":12240,"text":"The auditorium was empty."},{"time":15040,"text":"It was lit only by the dim, green glow\nof the emergency exit sign."},{"time":20200,"text":"This was the most\nexciting day of Vera's life."},{"time":24160,"text":"She was the youngest\nconcert promoter in Germany,"},{"time":27200,"text":"and she had persuaded\nthe Cologne Opera House"},{"time":29640,"text":"to host a late-night concert of jazz"},{"time":33000,"text":"from the American musician, Keith Jarrett."},{"time":36800,"text":"1,400 people were coming."},{"time":39840,"text":"And in just a few hours,"},{"time":41440,"text":"Jarrett would walk out on the same stage,"},{"time":43880,"text":"he'd sit down at the piano"},{"time":45240,"text":"and without rehearsal or sheet music,"},{"time":49080,"text":"he would begin to play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52320,"text":"But right now,"},{"time":53560,"text":"Vera was introducing Keith\nto the piano in question,"},{"time":57160,"text":"and it wasn't going well."},{"time":59120,"text":"Jarrett looked to the instrument\na little warily,"},{"time":61800,"text":"played a few notes,"},{"time":63360,"text":"walked around it,"},{"time":64599,"text":"played a few more notes,"},{"time":66080,"text":"muttered something to his producer."},{"time":67800,"text":"Then the producer\ncame over to Vera and said ..."},{"time":72280,"text":"\"If you don't get a new piano,\nKeith can't play.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"There'd been a mistake."},{"time":79480,"text":"The opera house had provided\nthe wrong instrument."},{"time":81880,"text":"This one had this harsh,\ntinny upper register,"},{"time":84560,"text":"because all the felt had worn away."},{"time":87640,"text":"The black notes were sticking,"},{"time":90800,"text":"the white notes were out of tune,"},{"time":92720,"text":"the pedals didn't work"},{"time":94400,"text":"and the piano itself was just too small."},{"time":96600,"text":"It wouldn't create the volume"},{"time":98040,"text":"that would fill a large space\nsuch as the Cologne Opera House."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102520,"text":"So Keith Jarrett left."},{"time":106400,"text":"He went and sat outside in his car,"},{"time":109040,"text":"leaving Vera Brandes"},{"time":111000,"text":"to get on the phone\nto try to find a replacement piano."},{"time":115680,"text":"Now she got a piano tuner,"},{"time":117320,"text":"but she couldn't get a new piano."},{"time":120160,"text":"And so she went outside"},{"time":122880,"text":"and she stood there in the rain,"},{"time":125520,"text":"talking to Keith Jarrett,"},{"time":128000,"text":"begging him not to cancel the concert."},{"time":132160,"text":"And he looked out of his car"},{"time":133600,"text":"at this bedraggled,\nrain-drenched German teenager,"},{"time":138280,"text":"took pity on her,"},{"time":140080,"text":"and said,"},{"time":141960,"text":"\"Never forget ... only for you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":147120,"text":"And so a few hours later,"},{"time":148920,"text":"Jarrett did indeed step out\nonto the stage of the opera house,"},{"time":153400,"text":"he sat down at the unplayable piano"},{"time":157600,"text":"and began."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159320,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172720,"text":"Within moments it became clear\nthat something magical was happening."},{"time":178080,"text":"Jarrett was avoiding\nthose upper registers,"},{"time":180680,"text":"he was sticking to the middle\ntones of the keyboard,"},{"time":183320,"text":"which gave the piece\na soothing, ambient quality."},{"time":187960,"text":"But also, because the piano was so quiet,"},{"time":190520,"text":"he had to set up these rumbling,\nrepetitive riffs in the bass."},{"time":194960,"text":"And he stood up twisting,\npounding down on the keys,"},{"time":200240,"text":"desperately trying to create enough volume\nto reach the people in the back row."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205880,"text":"It's an electrifying performance."},{"time":207920,"text":"It somehow has this peaceful quality,"},{"time":210880,"text":"and at the same time it's full of energy,"},{"time":212960,"text":"it's dynamic."},{"time":215200,"text":"And the audience loved it."},{"time":217560,"text":"Audiences continue to love it"},{"time":219240,"text":"because the recording of the KÃ¶ln Concert"},{"time":222360,"text":"is the best-selling piano album in history"},{"time":224880,"text":"and the best-selling\nsolo jazz album in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230560,"text":"Keith Jarrett had been handed a mess."},{"time":234280,"text":"He had embraced that mess, and it soared."},{"time":240520,"text":"But let's think for a moment\nabout Jarrett's initial instinct."},{"time":245360,"text":"He didn't want to play."},{"time":246960,"text":"Of course,"},{"time":248200,"text":"I think any of us,\nin any remotely similar situation,"},{"time":251160,"text":"would feel the same way,\nwe'd have the same instinct."},{"time":253760,"text":"We don't want to be asked\nto do good work with bad tools."},{"time":257079,"text":"We don't want to have to overcome\nunnecessary hurdles."},{"time":262160,"text":"But Jarrett's instinct was wrong,"},{"time":265120,"text":"and thank goodness he changed his mind."},{"time":267840,"text":"And I think our instinct is also wrong."},{"time":272800,"text":"I think we need to gain\na bit more appreciation"},{"time":276240,"text":"for the unexpected advantages\nof having to cope with a little mess."},{"time":283560,"text":"So let me give you some examples"},{"time":285720,"text":"from cognitive psychology,"},{"time":288200,"text":"from complexity science,"},{"time":289640,"text":"from social psychology,"},{"time":291120,"text":"and of course, rock 'n' roll."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293680,"text":"So cognitive psychology first."},{"time":295760,"text":"We've actually known for a while"},{"time":297600,"text":"that certain kinds of difficulty,"},{"time":299960,"text":"certain kinds of obstacle,"},{"time":301560,"text":"can actually improve our performance."},{"time":303346,"text":"For example,"},{"time":305080,"text":"the psychologist Daniel Oppenheimer,"},{"time":306840,"text":"a few years ago,"},{"time":308080,"text":"teamed up with high school teachers."},{"time":310160,"text":"And he asked them to reformat the handouts"},{"time":312920,"text":"that they were giving\nto some of their classes."},{"time":316200,"text":"So the regular handout would be formatted\nin something straightforward,"},{"time":319558,"text":"such as Helvetica or Times New Roman."},{"time":322840,"text":"But half these classes were getting\nhandouts that were formatted"},{"time":325880,"text":"in something sort of intense,\nlike Haettenschweiler,"},{"time":329600,"text":"or something with a zesty bounce,\nlike Comic Sans italicized."},{"time":333640,"text":"Now, these are really ugly fonts,"},{"time":335480,"text":"and they're difficult fonts to read."},{"time":337680,"text":"But at the end of the semester,"},{"time":339800,"text":"students were given exams,"},{"time":342440,"text":"and the students who'd been asked\nto read the more difficult fonts,"},{"time":346120,"text":"had actually done better on their exams,"},{"time":348200,"text":"in a variety of subjects."},{"time":349760,"text":"And the reason is,"},{"time":351800,"text":"the difficult font had slowed them down,"},{"time":354360,"text":"forced them to work a bit harder,"},{"time":356440,"text":"to think a bit more\nabout what they were reading,"},{"time":359040,"text":"to interpret it ..."},{"time":361360,"text":"and so they learned more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364320,"text":"Another example."},{"time":366760,"text":"The psychologist Shelley Carson\nhas been testing Harvard undergraduates"},{"time":371880,"text":"for the quality\nof their attentional filters."},{"time":374880,"text":"What do I mean by that?"},{"time":376280,"text":"What I mean is,\nimagine you're in a restaurant,"},{"time":378520,"text":"you're having a conversation,"},{"time":380280,"text":"there are all kinds of other conversations\ngoing on in the restaurant,"},{"time":383440,"text":"you want to filter them out,"},{"time":384800,"text":"you want to focus\non what's important to you."},{"time":386960,"text":"Can you do that?"},{"time":388200,"text":"If you can, you have\ngood, strong attentional filters."},{"time":391200,"text":"But some people really struggle with that."},{"time":393280,"text":"Some of Carson's undergraduate\nsubjects struggled with that."},{"time":397040,"text":"They had weak filters,\nthey had porous filters --"},{"time":400000,"text":"let a lot of external information in."},{"time":403400,"text":"And so what that meant is they were\nconstantly being interrupted"},{"time":406560,"text":"by the sights and the sounds\nof the world around them."},{"time":409160,"text":"If there was a television on\nwhile they were doing their essays,"},{"time":412240,"text":"they couldn't screen it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413680,"text":"Now, you would think\nthat that was a disadvantage ..."},{"time":417480,"text":"but no."},{"time":418720,"text":"When Carson looked at what\nthese students had achieved,"},{"time":422720,"text":"the ones with the weak filters"},{"time":424520,"text":"were vastly more likely"},{"time":426960,"text":"to have some real\ncreative milestone in their lives,"},{"time":429760,"text":"to have published their first novel,"},{"time":432120,"text":"to have released their first album."},{"time":435200,"text":"These distractions were actually\ngrists to their creative mill."},{"time":438920,"text":"They were able to think outside the box\nbecause their box was full of holes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444200,"text":"Let's talk about complexity science."},{"time":445960,"text":"So how do you solve a really complex --"},{"time":447842,"text":"the world's full\nof complicated problems --"},{"time":449880,"text":"how do you solve\na really complicated problem?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452080,"text":"For example, you try to make a jet engine."},{"time":454240,"text":"There are lots and lots\nof different variables,"},{"time":456480,"text":"the operating temperature, the materials,"},{"time":458457,"text":"all the different dimensions, the shape."},{"time":460920,"text":"You can't solve that kind\nof problem all in one go,"},{"time":463480,"text":"it's too hard."},{"time":464720,"text":"So what do you do?"},{"time":465960,"text":"Well, one thing you can do\nis try to solve it step-by-step."},{"time":470920,"text":"So you have some kind of prototype"},{"time":472640,"text":"and you tweak it,\nyou test it, you improve it."},{"time":476080,"text":"You tweak it, you test it, you improve it."},{"time":480040,"text":"Now, this idea of marginal gains\nwill eventually get you a good jet engine."},{"time":485560,"text":"And it's been quite widely\nimplemented in the world."},{"time":488880,"text":"So you'll hear about it, for example,\nin high performance cycling,"},{"time":492400,"text":"web designers will talk about trying\nto optimize their web pages,"},{"time":495720,"text":"they're looking\nfor these step-by-step gains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498040,"text":"That's a good way\nto solve a complicated problem."},{"time":502440,"text":"But you know what would\nmake it a better way?"},{"time":506600,"text":"A dash of mess."},{"time":509320,"text":"You add randomness,"},{"time":511360,"text":"early on in the process,"},{"time":512760,"text":"you make crazy moves,"},{"time":514280,"text":"you try stupid things that shouldn't work,"},{"time":517679,"text":"and that will tend to make\nthe problem-solving work better."},{"time":520720,"text":"And the reason for that is"},{"time":522280,"text":"the trouble with the step-by-step process,"},{"time":524360,"text":"the marginal gains,"},{"time":525600,"text":"is they can walk you\ngradually down a dead end."},{"time":529160,"text":"And if you start with the randomness,\nthat becomes less likely,"},{"time":533400,"text":"and your problem-solving\nbecomes more robust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538440,"text":"Let's talk about social psychology."},{"time":540720,"text":"So the psychologist Katherine Phillips,\nwith some colleagues,"},{"time":543840,"text":"recently gave murder mystery\nproblems to some students,"},{"time":547920,"text":"and these students\nwere collected in groups of four"},{"time":550800,"text":"and they were given dossiers\nwith information about a crime --"},{"time":554160,"text":"alibis and evidence,\nwitness statements and three suspects."},{"time":559000,"text":"And the groups of four students\nwere asked to figure out who did it,"},{"time":563200,"text":"who committed the crime."},{"time":565280,"text":"And there were two treatments\nin this experiment."},{"time":568760,"text":"In some cases these were four friends,"},{"time":572000,"text":"they all knew each other well."},{"time":574160,"text":"In other cases,"},{"time":575960,"text":"three friends and a stranger."},{"time":579040,"text":"And you can see where I'm going with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581120,"text":"Obviously I'm going to say"},{"time":582400,"text":"that the groups with the stranger\nsolved the problem more effectively,"},{"time":585840,"text":"which is true, they did."},{"time":587800,"text":"Actually, they solved the problem\nquite a lot more effectively."},{"time":591320,"text":"So the groups of four friends,"},{"time":595120,"text":"they only had a 50-50 chance\nof getting the answer right."},{"time":598120,"text":"Which is actually not that great --"},{"time":599840,"text":"in multiple choice, for three answers?\n50-50's not good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":604000,"text":"The three friends and the stranger,"},{"time":605720,"text":"even though the stranger\ndidn't have any extra information,"},{"time":608560,"text":"even though it was just a case"},{"time":610120,"text":"of how that changed the conversation\nto accommodate that awkwardness,"},{"time":616440,"text":"the three friends and the stranger,"},{"time":618160,"text":"they had a 75 percent chance\nof finding the right answer."},{"time":620850,"text":"That's quite a big leap in performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622600,"text":"But I think what's really interesting"},{"time":624960,"text":"is not just that the three friends\nand the stranger did a better job,"},{"time":628223,"text":"but how they felt about it."},{"time":630400,"text":"So when Katherine Phillips\ninterviewed the groups of four friends,"},{"time":635360,"text":"they had a nice time,"},{"time":637240,"text":"they also thought they'd done a good job."},{"time":640720,"text":"They were complacent."},{"time":642800,"text":"When she spoke to the three\nfriends and the stranger,"},{"time":645320,"text":"they had not had a nice time --"},{"time":646840,"text":"it's actually rather difficult,\nit's rather awkward ..."},{"time":650480,"text":"and they were full of doubt."},{"time":654200,"text":"They didn't think they'd done a good job\neven though they had."},{"time":658080,"text":"And I think that really exemplifies"},{"time":659840,"text":"the challenge that we're\ndealing with here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662680,"text":"Because, yeah --"},{"time":664520,"text":"the ugly font,"},{"time":666400,"text":"the awkward stranger,"},{"time":668200,"text":"the random move ..."},{"time":670280,"text":"these disruptions help us solve problems,"},{"time":673680,"text":"they help us become more creative."},{"time":676040,"text":"But we don't feel that they're helping us."},{"time":678120,"text":"We feel that they're\ngetting in the way ..."},{"time":681040,"text":"and so we resist."},{"time":684000,"text":"And that's why the last example\nis really important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687360,"text":"So I want to talk about somebody"},{"time":689600,"text":"from the background\nof the world of rock 'n' roll."},{"time":694560,"text":"And you may know him,\nhe's actually a TED-ster."},{"time":697480,"text":"His name is Brian Eno."},{"time":698880,"text":"He is an ambient composer --\nrather brilliant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701720,"text":"He's also a kind of catalyst"},{"time":705160,"text":"behind some of the great\nrock 'n' roll albums of the last 40 years."},{"time":709200,"text":"He's worked with David Bowie on \"Heroes,\""},{"time":712840,"text":"he worked with U2 on \"Achtung Baby\"\nand \"The Joshua Tree,\""},{"time":716000,"text":"he's worked with DEVO,"},{"time":717560,"text":"he's worked with Coldplay,\nhe's worked with everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720160,"text":"And what does he do to make\nthese great rock bands better?"},{"time":725720,"text":"Well, he makes a mess."},{"time":727840,"text":"He disrupts their creative processes."},{"time":729680,"text":"It's his role to be the awkward stranger."},{"time":731800,"text":"It's his role to tell them"},{"time":733240,"text":"that they have to play\nthe unplayable piano."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736440,"text":"And one of the ways\nin which he creates this disruption"},{"time":739120,"text":"is through this remarkable\ndeck of cards --"},{"time":742680,"text":"I have my signed copy here --\nthank you, Brian."},{"time":746560,"text":"They're called The Oblique Strategies,"},{"time":748440,"text":"he developed them with a friend of his."},{"time":750800,"text":"And when they're stuck in the studio,"},{"time":754880,"text":"Brian Eno will reach for one of the cards."},{"time":757200,"text":"He'll draw one at random,"},{"time":758680,"text":"and he'll make the band\nfollow the instructions on the card."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762960,"text":"So this one ..."},{"time":765040,"text":"\"Change instrument roles.\""},{"time":766360,"text":"Yeah, everyone swap instruments --\nDrummer on the piano --"},{"time":769099,"text":"Brilliant, brilliant idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771120,"text":"\"Look closely at the most \nembarrassing details. Amplify them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":776360,"text":"\"Make a sudden, destructive,\nunpredictable action. Incorporate.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":782960,"text":"These cards are disruptive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785080,"text":"Now, they've proved their worth\nin album after album."},{"time":789880,"text":"The musicians hate them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":793720,"text":"So Phil Collins was playing drums\non an early Brian Eno album."},{"time":797160,"text":"He got so frustrated he started\nthrowing beer cans across the studio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802400,"text":"Carlos Alomar, great rock guitarist,"},{"time":804800,"text":"working with Eno\non David Bowie's \"Lodger\" album,"},{"time":808600,"text":"and at one point\nhe turns to Brian and says,"},{"time":811200,"text":"\"Brian, this experiment is stupid.\""},{"time":817360,"text":"But the thing is\nit was a pretty good album,"},{"time":821120,"text":"but also,"},{"time":823040,"text":"Carlos Alomar, 35 years later,\nnow uses The Oblique Strategies."},{"time":827880,"text":"And he tells his students\nto use The Oblique Strategies"},{"time":830640,"text":"because he's realized something."},{"time":833240,"text":"Just because you don't like it\ndoesn't mean it isn't helping you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"The strategies actually\nweren't a deck of cards originally,"},{"time":842786,"text":"they were just a list --"},{"time":844000,"text":"list on the recording studio wall."},{"time":845840,"text":"A checklist of things\nyou might try if you got stuck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851280,"text":"The list didn't work."},{"time":854160,"text":"Know why?"},{"time":857400,"text":"Not messy enough."},{"time":859680,"text":"Your eye would go down the list"},{"time":861720,"text":"and it would settle on whatever\nwas the least disruptive,"},{"time":865800,"text":"the least troublesome,"},{"time":868480,"text":"which of course misses the point entirely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874160,"text":"And what Brian Eno came to realize was,"},{"time":876560,"text":"yes, we need to run\nthe stupid experiments,"},{"time":881080,"text":"we need to deal\nwith the awkward strangers,"},{"time":883160,"text":"we need to try to read the ugly fonts."},{"time":885320,"text":"These things help us."},{"time":886600,"text":"They help us solve problems,"},{"time":888000,"text":"they help us be more creative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889920,"text":"But also ..."},{"time":892320,"text":"we really need some persuasion\nif we're going to accept this."},{"time":896200,"text":"So however we do it ..."},{"time":898400,"text":"whether it's sheer willpower,"},{"time":900480,"text":"whether it's the flip of a card"},{"time":903560,"text":"or whether it's a guilt trip\nfrom a German teenager,"},{"time":907680,"text":"all of us, from time to time,"},{"time":909840,"text":"need to sit down and try and play\nthe unplayable piano."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915640,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916880,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}